Senator professor Nora Ladi Daduut has charged her constituents and the rest of Nigerians to remain committed to virtues that promote peace, unity and progress in Nigeria. Senator Dadu’ut in her Easter message which was made available to Sunday Independent in Jos, felicitated with her Christians in her Constituency, as they join their brethren across the world in celebrating Easter . Dadu’ut urged them to imbibe the teachings of Jesus Christ in their conduct and relationship with others. Senator Daduut called on her constituents to be vigilant about events happening around their environment. She assured that whatever challenges confronting the Nigeria Nation at the moment, the people wouldb soon be overcome them, Dadu’ut stressed. Daduut also reminded Christians that the death of Jesus Christ and his resurrection on Easter Sunday gives hope to a world in need of physical and spiritual healing. The Senator appealed to all to practise the Christian virtues of sacrifice, patience, love and abiding faith in order for us as Nigerians to have a better tomorrow which has been symbolized in the death and resurrection of Jesus Christ. Senator Daduut also lauded the Plateau state Governor Simon Lalong for this efforts at uniting the people of Plateau and called on citizens to support him at all times.